109 da indi in giuso è tutto ferro eletto, 110 salvo che ’l destro piede è terra cotta; 111 e sta ’n su quel, più che ’n su l’altro, eretto.

query.result:
**English:**

106 His head is formed of fine gold,
107 and pure silver are his arms and chest,
108 then he is of bronze down to the fork;

109 from there down he is all of fine iron,
110 except that his right foot is baked clay;
111 and he stands on that, more erect than on the other.

**Old English:**

106 His heafod is of fine golde geworht,
107 and his earmas and his breost of seolfre,
108 ðonne is he of coper oð ða lenden;

109 ðonne is he of iserne oð ða fet;
110 buton ðæt his swiðre fot is of claie;
111 and he stent on ðæm maran ðonne on ðæm oðrum.

**English:**

115 Their course in this valley is hurled downwards;
116 they make Acheron, Styx, and Phlegethon;
117 then they go down through this narrow channel,

118 until, where it is no longer possible to descend further,
119 they make Cocytus; and what that marsh is like
120 you will see, but here it is not told.

**Old English:**

115 Hiora rynn on ðisse denu niðerweard;
116 ða wyrðað Acheron, Styx and Flegeton;
117 ðonne ða fleoðað niðer ðurh ðone enge drorene,

118 oð ðæt ða cumað ðær ðær me ne mæg furðor;
119 ða wyrðað Cocytus; and hu ðæt wæter sie
120 ðu scealt ðær geseon, ac her hit ne secgað.
